<h1 class="HFheader"><img src="images/hostFamily/HF_arrow.png" width="18" height="15" alt="arrow" />RULES AND EXPECTATIONS</h1>

<ul> <li>BE REALISTIC AND AGE APPROPRIATE IN SETTING RULES FOR YOUR STUDENT.</li>
 <li>Lay out the rules carefully from curfews to expected family times.</li>
 <li>Don't assume that the student will know the way you want things done including:</li>
<ul><ol>- laundry</ol>
<ol>- shower times</ol>
<ol>- meal time</ol>
<ol>- chores</ol></ul>
 <li>The student should adhere to your rules and expectations but they cannot do that if you do not let them
know what you expect.</li>
 <li>Does the student understand your expectations? Talk about it up front with the student.</li>
 <li>If you have expectations for your children, communicate them to your exchange student so everyone's
chores are understood.</li>
 <li>Communicate with your ISE Area Representative if there are any concerns.</li></ul><br />
